<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="et">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/admin-panel.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/navbar.css" />
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    type="text/css"
    href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/slick-carousel/1.8.1/slick.min.css"
  />
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    type="text/css"
    href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/slick-carousel/1.8.1/slick-theme.min.css"
  />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com"/>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin/>
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@100..900&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css"
  />
  <title>Project Fullview</title>
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar">
    <img src="/img/proovikivi_logo.png" alt="proovikivi logo" />
    <button class="hamburger" id="hamburger">
      <i class="fas fa-bars"></i>
    </button>
    <div class="menu" id="menu">
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/project-form">Loo projekt</a></li>
        <li><a href="/projects">Projektid</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://proovikivi.ee/portfoolio/">Proovikivid</a></li>
        <li><a href="/profile">Minu profiil</a></li>
        <li><a href="/logout">Logi välja</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div>
    <h1>Admin: Populate Lookup Tables</h1>
    <p>
      Paste or type one entry per line into each of the fields below. When you
      click “Submit,” the server will:
      <ol>
        <li>Split each box by newline.</li>
        <li>Trim out any empty lines.</li>
        <li>Issue the corresponding INSERT statements for each table.</li>
      </ol>
      If any rows already exist (e.g. you ran this before), the backend should
      be prepared to either skip duplicates or update as needed.
    </p>

    <form action="/admin/panel" method="POST">
      <fieldset>
        <legend>1) Genders</legend>
        <label for="genders">Enter one gender per line:</label>
        <textarea id="genders" name="genders">
            <%= genders.map(row => row.name).join('\n') %>
        </textarea
        >
        <div class="help">
          – The “gender” table has columns (id, name).<br />
          – The server will insert each non‐blank line as a new “name”
          row. <br />
          – If you want to change or add more options, simply edit or append
          lines here.
        </div>
      </fieldset>

      <fieldset>
        <legend>2) User Types</legend>
        <label for="userTypes">Enter one user‐type per line:</label>
        <textarea id="userTypes" name="userTypes">
            <%= userTypes.map(row => row.name).join('\n') %>
        </textarea>
        <div class="help">
          – The “user_type” table is AUTO_INCREMENT on “id,” so we only need to
          supply “name.”<br />
          – Add or remove lines to control which user types exist.
        </div>
      </fieldset>

      <!-- 
        FIELDSET 3: School Subjects
        Each line becomes INSERT INTO school_subject (name) VALUES ('line');
      -->
      <fieldset>
        <legend>3) School Subjects</legend>
        <label for="schoolSubjects">Enter one subject per line:</label>
        <textarea id="schoolSubjects" name="schoolSubjects">
            <%= schoolSubjects.map(row => row.name).join('\n') %>
        </textarea>
        <div class="help">
          – Each non‐empty line becomes one row in `school_subject(name)`. <br />
          – Leave blank lines out (they will be skipped).
        </div>
      </fieldset>

      <fieldset>
        <legend>4) Global Goals (Proovikivi “Üleilmne eesmärk”)</legend>
        <label for="globalGoals"
          >Enter one global goal title per line (images will be empty):</label
        >
        <textarea id="globalGoals" name="globalGoals">
            <%= globalGoals.map(row => row.title).join('\n') %>
        </textarea
        >
        <div class="help">
          – Because `global_goal.image` is a BLOB and NOT NULL, the backend will
          insert an empty blob (`''`) by default. <br />
          – Each line here becomes a new `title` in the `global_goal` table.
        </div>
      </fieldset>

      <fieldset>
        <legend>5) Proovikivid (Project Ideas)</legend>
        <label for="proovikivid"
          >Enter one project (proovikivi) title per line. (Image = empty,
          goal = NULL.)</label
        >
        <textarea id="proovikivid" name="proovikivid">
            <%= proovikivid.map(row => row.title).join('\n') %>
        </textarea>

        <div class="help">
          – The `proovikivi` table has columns `(id, title, image, goal)`.  
          – We insert `title` from each line; `image` becomes an empty BLOB
          (`''`) and `goal` is set to `NULL`.  
          – Add or remove lines here to control the “project ideas” in the
          database.
        </div>
      </fieldset>

      <fieldset>
        <legend>6) Locations (Asukohad)</legend>
        <label for="locations">Enter one location per line:</label>
        <textarea id="locations" name="locations">
            <%= locations.map(row => row.name).join('\n') %>
        </textarea>
        <div class="help">
          – Each non‐empty line becomes one row in `location(name)`.  
          – Adjust as needed to add or remove counties/cities.
        </div>
      </fieldset>

      <button type="submit">Submit All Lookup Values</button>
    </form>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
